div.p:
The essence of the attached paper is:
The United States is now in a war of survival;
The United States is losing that war;
Therefore, the direction of all United States planning and the tempo of United States action should be revised toward the survival of the United States and its allies, and toward a concurrent
program of political action so that at the end of this war the people of the free world will be organized to prevent a future war.

The purposes of the Soviet are now crystal clear to the world;
                                        but the purposes of this country and its allies are not
                                        clear.
